July 8, 1981
.LP
This package is an update of the 4.1bsd release, for which you received
a complete distribution before.
.LP
The printed materials are:
.IP *
A new revision of Installing/ Operating 4.1bsd
.IP *
A new revision of Changes in the Kernel in 4.1bsd
.IP *
A survey of resources and needs
.IP *
A few updated manual pages
.IP *
A new Lisp Users Manual
.IP *
A newsletter about additions or changes to 4.1bsd
.IP *
Our proposal for UNIX enhancements
.IP *
A few papers on UNIX vs VMS performance
.LP
The newsletter is a collection of bug fixes contributed by many sources.
We appreciate the feedback on the bugs you have found.
Unfortunately, we cannot always responsed to every message.
The more serious problems found will be outlined in future newsletters.
The remaining reports will be integrated into future releases.
.LP
Bug reports about this distribution can be mailed to
``arpavax.4bsd-bugs@berkeley'' on the ARPANET, or to ``ucbvax!4bsd-bugs''
on the uucp network (you will have to figure out how to get to ucbvax
on the uucp net).  Ideas for improvement of the system should be sent
to ``4bsd-ideas'', in the same network context.
Please let us know of problems you have with the distribution tape.
If you bring up new devices or other software which you would be willing
to share with others, let us know.
